.git
.worktrees
target
node_modules
features
frontend
# Keep the editor frontend's manifest: the admin and lawmaking image builds run
# the npm-workspace `npm ci`, which needs every workspace package.json present.
# (The editor image itself uses frontend/Dockerfile.dockerignore, not this file.)
!frontend/package.json
doc
*.md
*.png
*.json
!package.json
!package-lock.json
!Cargo.toml
!Cargo.lock
# The note (annotation) JSON schema is embedded at compile time by
# regelrecht-corpus (annotation-validation feature) in the editor-api
# image build. The blanket *.json exclude above would drop it from the
# build context; re-include the schema tree so `include_str!` resolves.
!schema
!schema/**
.vscode
.idea
# Exclude .claude but keep skill files needed by the enrich worker image.
# Docker requires un-excluding each path component from parent to child.
.claude
!.claude/skills
.claude/skills/*
!.claude/skills/law-generate
!.claude/skills/law-mvt-research
!.claude/skills/law-reverse-validate
.pytest_cache
__pycache__
.github
